I placed an order through Uber Eats because I clearly didn’t want to leave my home- I paid a processing fee and a delivery fee for the convenience. Unfortunately when my order arrived, one of the two sandwiches I ordered was missing. The bag was sealed and I spoke to the driver, who had no responsibility in the situation, and he told me to contact the restaurant. I sent in a complaint through Uber and was promptly refunded for the price of the sandwich, and nothing more. I get that that is on Uber. But now I was out my dinner. I called and spoke to another employee who tried to help me the best he could before he transferred me to his manager Juan. After explaining my situation, I had hoped the restaurant would take responsibility for the missing sandwich, but Juan refused. My Uber delivery guy didn’t steal a sandwich man, your staff messed up and now i’m out my dinner. All he could tell me was that if I traveled to the location, the very thing I paid a convenience fee to avoid, he would be able to comp the sandwich for me. Otherwise I would have to reorder through uber, pay another delivery and convenience fee, and receive nothing in return for my troubles. I tried to be understanding as I work in retail myself and loathe being an annoying customer, but I was surprised at how unwilling Juan was in taking responsibility for the restaurant’s error. Rude.

So I just got some more food from another restaurant. Then, I went and picked up my order from Nando's (supposedly everything but the chicken livers) and there were in fact chicken livers in there but no fries. So now I paid for extra food which I didn't need and I don't have any sides.  I don't usually care for petty things like this and I almost never leave bad reviews but like I said - this is the 3rd time my order has been wrong in the total of 4 times I've gotten food from here and I'm frustrated. So if you are one of those people that say "surprise me" to their waiter at a restaurant then by all means - order from this Nando's. Where do I begin...  This place is heaven on earth and I don’t use those words lightly. This place is truly a paradise. I live out of town but I’ll always make my way to this joint when I’m in Chicago.  The place is always clean. Looks very tropical and has an earthy feel to the furniture. The table wood is nicely crafted and feels sturdy when I chow down on my food.  Speaking of food, it amplifies my experience to exponential levels... Especially the chicken. The chicken is grilled indoors. The flames slowly burning the chicken to cement the flavor of the marinade on the chicken. The flavor roars when you bite into it. It has the perfect combination of spices and flavorings to balance being on a flame grill. Add a flame grilled corn on the cob and fries with that chicken and I guarantee you will have mini orgasms exploding in your mouth.  The sauce is packaged into bottles and it gives you the flexibility to add more spices to your food. The extra sauce can be used for dipping your fries or adding more flavor to the chicken. Either way, the sauce should be illegal given how highly addictive this sauce is.  I have sent numerous requests to Peri-Peri chicken corporate to see if I can open a franchise because it’s how much I believe in this food and restaurant.

I come here regularly considering that I work in the area and tend to get lunch from here time to time. Usually my food is always ready by the time I get to the restaurant since I take to go orders. My food is always hot, well cooked and very flavorful. However, I ordered the chicken breast sandwich on 4/3 around 2pm. Ten minutes after ordering I had already made it to the restaurant and observed there was only one table of two in the entire establishment. Not busy at all. When I got back to the office my sandwich and fries were COLD and did not seem fresh at all. It felt like they had the chicken sitting there for a while and prepared whatever they had ready. I will not be going back to this particular location for a long time. It’s not that hard to get a sandwich right especially if it’s not lunch rush. They also need to get better with their cleanliness in the condiments section. Every bottle when poured is very greasy to the touch. They should consider wiping the sauce bottles more often. I love me some peri peri chicken but having to eat it barely warm enough, made me sick. I give the chain 5 stars as a whole, but this location 1.

I would rather have a waiter take my order and serve me, and check back periodically. Specially if tipping is involved. Customers are required to go to the front register Everytime they wish to order or ask a question. Overall: Easy go-to option for some quick delicious chicken options with flair.  The good: Like most Nando's, the atmosphere is really fun and inviting. They have hanging chairs mock can and wood-splint furniture, which is comfortable and unique. The menu is vast and varies, and the sauces have great flavors ranging from mild, spicy, tangy, or sweet. The portions are good sized for the main courses and the chicken and sides are tasty.  The bad: The chicken pitas don't have nearly enough chicken on them, primarily veggies. The prices are too expensive for what you get. They aren't too bad, but if you get more than a regular item it can be more expensive than it needs to be.  Atmosphere: 8/10 Service: 8/10 Food: 8/10

Tasty! I got the chicken thighs and mashed potatoes with medium spice level because I'm a lot wimpier than my friends when it comes to spicy food but I still thought it was flavorful. My friend got the 1/2 chicken and chips in hot and liked her dish as well. The chicken was cooked wonderfully and the mashed potatoes are my favorite side at nandos.  A few tips, try the sauces at the sauce station before you order if you're not sure how spicy you want your food to be. Also the boneless chicken options say so in the menu, so if there it doesn't say "boneless" expect bones.  Another thing, some of the servers were very friendly, others not so much. One just acted like she didn't want to be there and was pretty rude, but maybe she was having a bad day.
